<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd281f763-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s386"><num value="386">§ 386.</num><heading> Forfeitures</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The following forfeitures shall apply to this part in addition to penalties and forfeitures provided by subchapter V of this chapter:</chapeau><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idd281f764-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s386/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> Any vessel of the United States that is navigated in violation of the provisions of this part or of the rules and regulations of the Commission made in pursuance thereof shall forfeit to the United States the sum of $5,000 recoverable by way of suit or libel. Each day during which such navigation occurs shall constitute a separate offense.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idd281f765-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s386/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> Every willful failure on the part of the master of a vessel of the United States to enforce or to comply with the provisions of this part or the rules and regulations of the Commission made in pursuance thereof shall cause him to forfeit to the United States the sum of $1,000.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idd281f766-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5">(<ref href="/us/act/1934-06-19/ch652">June 19, 1934, ch. 652</ref>, title III, § 386, as added <ref href="/us/act/1956-08-06/ch973/s1">Aug. 6, 1956, ch. 973, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70/1048">70 Stat. 1048</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/101/239/tIII/s3002/h">Pub. L. 101–239, title III, § 3002(h)</ref>, <date date="1989-12-19">Dec. 19, 1989</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/103/2131">103 Stat. 2131</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/414/tIII/s303/a/20/F">Pub. L. 103–414, title III, § 303(a)(20)(F)</ref>, <date date="1994-10-25">Oct. 25, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4295">108 Stat. 4295</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
